DESCRIPTION OF YOUR CLASS DESIGN AND ALGORITHMS AND DATA STRUCTURES USED:

WordFinder:
This class has a main that's responsible for processing the command-line argument
, and handling any error processing. It also has the main command loop.
This class calls ScoreCalculator class to find all words and their score from racks,
and only depends on the ScoreCalculator.

ScoreCalculator:
The class I made.
It calculates the scores of all the subset of rack.
To achieve this, it uses AnagramDictionary to find all legal word combinations of Rack
and uses information in ScoreTable to calculates the scores.
It doesn't process any command-line argument or handle any error processing.
WordFinder does and passes needed information to it.

Rack
This corresponds to the idea of the rack in the problem description.
Thus,This class stores the letters and find all subsets of rack.

AnagramDictionary
This contains the dictionary data organized by anagrams.
It reads all the words in dictionary to a Map and helps to find all anagrams of a string

ScoreTable
This class has information about Scrabble scores for scrabble letters and words by hard-coding in its data.
It helps to find score of a string


